    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span><strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>[130ml] <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>massaman paste</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>massaman sauce</strong></p><p>Once thickened, transfer the <strong>massaman sauce</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and gently stir it all together</p><p>Set aside to cool until serving (reserve the pan!) \u2013 this is your <strong>massaman salad dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a high heat with a small drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then add your <strong>green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong>, <strong>drained green beans</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>massaman salad dressing</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and toss \u2013 this is your <strong>massaman-style salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/massaman-style-chicken-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>massaman-style salad</strong> and top with the <strong>cooked chicken</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining massaman dressing </strong>and garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds </strong>and <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
